CM1 Exam Problem: Markov Chains
An analyst uses the following three-state model to model career progression at a company.
You will find an Excel file, an R file, and the LaTeX file showing the solution. The R file provides a visual explanation of why those arguments are included in Part II.

The analyst makes the following assumptions:
• The salary of a trainee is $20,000 p.a. payable continuously.
• The salary of a manager is $35,000 p.a. payable continuously.
• Aone-off bonus of $15,000 is payable immediately on promotion to manager.
• The maximum term of employment at the company is 30 years.
• The force of interest is 5% p.a.
Denote tpijx as the probability that an employee in state i at age x is in state j at age x + t.
(i) Write down an expression in integral form, using the probabilities and forces of transition,
for the expected present value of the future salary payable to an employee aged 35 exact who
has just joined the company as a trainee.
(ii) Explain how the expected value expressed in part (i) would change if, for all x:
(a) σx increases.
(b) µx increases.
